<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>KeepUp Billing Terms</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/legal-page.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="no-nav bg-light legal-page">
    <main class="container py-5">
      <section class="legal-shell mx-auto">
        <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 legal-hero mb-4">
          <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
            <p class="legal-kicker mb-2">KeepUp CRM</p>
            <h1 class="display-6 mb-3">Billing Terms</h1>
            <p class="lead text-secondary mb-3">
              These Billing Terms describe how paid KeepUp subscriptions, seats, and optional services are billed.
            </p>
            <p class="legal-updated mb-0">
              <strong>Last Updated:</strong> <%= lastUpdated %>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card shadow-sm border-0">
          <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
            <div class="legal-copy">
              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="billing-overview">
                <h2 id="billing-overview">Subscription Services Overview</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp offers subscription-based access to CRM, workflow, and related builder-facing software services.
                  Paid access may include company-level subscriptions, seat-based charges, and optional add-ons or service
                  modules shown in an order form, proposal, invoice, checkout flow, or billing interface.
                </p>
                <p>
                  These Billing Terms apply to KeepUp only. If a separate order form, proposal, invoice, or other written
                  agreement includes specific pricing or commercial terms, that document controls over these general terms
                  to the extent of any conflict.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="pricing-order-terms">
                <h2 id="pricing-order-terms">Pricing, Order Forms, and Billing UI</h2>
                <p>
                  Pricing may be presented in a KeepUp billing screen, checkout session, proposal, order form, invoice,
                  or other written communication. The pricing shown at the time of purchase or renewal, together with any
                  custom minimums, included quantities, waived charges, or promotional terms confirmed by KeepUp, forms part
                  of your subscription arrangement.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Some accounts may be billed directly through a self-serve payment flow, while others may be managed by
                  KeepUp with billing details handled outside the self-serve UI. Both arrangements remain subject to these
                  Billing Terms unless a separate written agreement states otherwise.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="recurring-billing">
                <h2 id="recurring-billing">Recurring Billing and Auto-Renewal</h2>
                <p>
                  Paid KeepUp subscriptions renew automatically on the billing cycle shown in the applicable billing flow,
                  invoice, or order form unless canceled in accordance with these terms. Recurring charges may continue until
                  the subscription or applicable service is canceled and the current billing period ends.
                </p>
                <p>
                  If KeepUp provides a self-serve payment method or subscription portal for your account, you authorize KeepUp
                  and its payment providers to charge the payment method on file for recurring subscription amounts and other
                  authorized charges when due.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="seats-usage">
                <h2 id="seats-usage">Seat-Based Billing and Minimum Billing Rules</h2>
                <p>
                  Where seat-based pricing applies, billing is based on the number of active users with login access, subject
                  to any minimum billed seat count shown in the billing UI, order form, or other agreed commercial terms.
                </p>
                <p>
                  KeepUp may calculate billable seats using active users, included minimums, and any custom billing policy or
                  override configured for the customer account. Seat counts used for billing do not necessarily limit the number
                  of invited users that can exist in the workspace unless expressly stated in writing.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="addons-services">
                <h2 id="addons-services">Add-Ons and Optional Services</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp may offer optional add-ons, integrations, community-based services, setup work, trials, or other
                  supplemental services. Those items may be billed separately from the base subscription and may be priced per
                  company, per community, per service, or on another basis shown in the applicable billing surface.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Activation of some optional services may require a request, approval, or configuration step before billing
                  begins. If a trial is offered, any billing consequences will be determined by the service status shown in the
                  applicable KeepUp workflow, billing UI, or written agreement.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="invoices-payment">
                <h2 id="invoices-payment">Invoicing and Payment Timing</h2>
                <p>
                  Subscription charges are due as billed. Depending on the account setup, KeepUp may collect payment through a
                  payment processor, bill on a recurring subscription basis, or issue invoices payable under the timing stated
                  in the applicable invoice, order form, or billing workflow.
                </p>
                <p>
                  One-time charges, add-on charges, setup fees, and prorated adjustments may be billed when incurred, when a
                  service is activated, or on the next billing cycle, depending on how the service is configured.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="cancellation">
                <h2 id="cancellation">Cancellation and When Cancellation Takes Effect</h2>
                <p>
                  If self-serve subscription management is available for your account, you may cancel through the billing portal
                  or other authorized KeepUp workflow. If billing is managed by KeepUp, cancellation may require notice to KeepUp
                  or submission of a cancellation request through the platform or support.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Unless otherwise stated in writing, cancellation stops future renewal charges after the end of the current paid
                  billing period and does not automatically create a refund for charges already billed. Some optional services may
                  remain active until operational shutdown or requested changes are completed.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="refunds">
                <h2 id="refunds">Refund Policy</h2>
                <p>
                  Fees paid to KeepUp are generally non-refundable except where required by law or expressly agreed by KeepUp in
                  writing. This includes subscription fees, add-on fees, setup fees, and other billed amounts unless a different
                  refund treatment is stated in the applicable order form or written agreement.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="suspension">
                <h2 id="suspension">Right to Suspend for Non-Payment</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp may suspend access to some or all services for overdue amounts, failed payments, chargebacks, or other
                  billing issues. Where appropriate, KeepUp may provide notice and an opportunity to cure before suspension, but
                  we are not required to delay suspension where doing so would create operational, contractual, or collection risk.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="taxes">
                <h2 id="taxes">Taxes and Fees</h2>
                <p>
                  Prices do not include taxes, duties, levies, withholding amounts, or similar government charges unless expressly
                  stated otherwise. The customer is responsible for applicable taxes and fees associated with the subscription,
                  excluding taxes based on KeepUp&rsquo;s net income.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="pricing-changes">
                <h2 id="pricing-changes">Changes to Pricing</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp may change pricing, packaging, included quantities, or billing policies from time to time. Any changes
                  will apply prospectively and, where appropriate, after notice through the platform, billing interface, invoice,
                  order form, email, or other reasonable communication channel.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="billing-contact">
                <h2 id="billing-contact">Billing Questions</h2>
                <p>
                  Questions about KeepUp billing, subscriptions, renewals, or cancellation may be sent to
                  <a href="mailto:<%= supportEmail %>"><%= supportEmail %></a>.
                </p>
              </section>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
